wikipedia_page.main: Henry William Haygarth (1821–1902) was an English cleric who as a young man lived for eight years in the Australian bush, writing a journal based on his experiences.

response: Haygarth was born in Hastings, Sussex. He was the youngest of three children of William Haygarth (1784–1825), who died before he was born, and his wife Frances Parry (1794–1886), with older brothers Henry William Haygarth and Colonel Francis Haygarth. Though only he out of his brothers would go on to play cricket, he also had two cousins John Haygarth and Edward Haygarth, who played.
